Reflection API:
------------------
-API to get class information
-To fetch Meta data about a class
-to get every detail of a class dynamically


 The Reflection API is mainly used in:

IDE (Integrated Development Environment) e.g. Eclipse, MyEclipse, NetBeans etc.
Debugger
Test Tools 
frameworks..[hibernate , springs ]



Class  - > is a class to hold class info

step1:
1.Create the class object for any class



  
import java.lang.reflect 

class Person{
  
}



public class Student extends Person{

}



1. Create class object for every class
ex:
		Class c = Person.class; 
		System.out.println(c.getName());
	
		Class c1 = Student.class;
		System.out.println(c.getName());
		





